description: The molecule is a disaccharide consisting beta-D-glucosyl and D-glucuronic acid residues joined by a (1->3)-linkage. It is a carbohydrate acid and a glycosylglucopyranuronic acid. It derives from a cellobiose. It is a conjugate acid of a 3-O-beta-D-glucosyl-D-glucuronate.

The molecule is an L-isoleucine derivative that is L-isoleucine bearing a (4S)-hydroxy substituent. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is an amino alcohol, a L-isoleucine derivative and a non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid. It is a tautomer of a (4S)-4-hydroxy-L-isoleucine zwitterion.
